cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as relation extraction. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and attention mechanisms also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of knowledge bases, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of deep learning techniques and the focus on improving performance suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
